Polyp. Capitular ridges conspicuous, 9–11 (Morphbank 830696 ). Tentacles, oral disk, and column of expanded polyps bright yellow (
Reimer et al . 2008 a
). Polyps of diameter 1.7–3.9 mm (contracted) extend up to 12 mm from coenenchyme; body wall infiltrated with foraminifer tests, sclerites, sediment, and spicules (
Reimer et al . 2008 a
). Tentacles 18–22 , dicyclic around oral disk 5.3–7.7 mm in expanded diameter (
Reimer et al . 2008 a
).
